    {
      "title": "Convert the table values",
      "content": "Since $g(x)=\\frac{f(x)}{x+4}$, multiply each $g(x)$ value by $x+4$ to get $f(x)$:$$f(-24)=3(-24+4)=-60$$$$f(-9)=0(-9+4)=0$$$$f(16)=5(16+4)=100$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Find the linear rule",
      "content": "Use the points $(-9,0)$ and $(16{,}100)$:$$m=\\frac{100-0}{16-(-9)}=\\frac{100}{25}=4$$With $f(x)=4x+b$ and $f(-9)=0$, solve:$$0=4(-9)+b$$$$b=36$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Read the intercept",
      "content": "The linear function is $f(x)=4x+36$, so the y-intercept is $(0,36)$. The answer is <strong>A</strong>."
    }
  ]
}
